{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"G3 container coverage audit (parent WS-EVAL-EXISTING vs this child 7402 + full sibling roster): clean — no findings.\n\n4-bucket audit of the parent's 5 acceptance criteria:\n- AC1 (3 packaged eval specs, validate_eval_spec-clean, disciplined judges, gold_set): STRUCTURAL for 7402; covered by sibling c156.\n- AC2 (deterministic-scorer registry; every scorer name -> pure fn; validate_scorer rejects unregistered): STRUCTURAL for 7402; covered by sibling 476f.\n- AC3 (run_eval() runs live via Inspect for all specs; the 3 agentic reviewers run via a context-injection solver + stubbed/fixture repo tools): PARTIALLY covered by 7402 — this child delivers exactly the context-injection solver + repo-tool stubbing + fixture corpus half (its ACs 1/2/4 + label adjudication). The \"run_eval() runs live via Inspect\" half is covered by sibling 4569. Union = fully covered.\n- AC4 (eval-discipline CI gates all 7 specs; offline tests assert dataset balance + non-empty gold_set): STRUCTURAL for 7402; covered by c156 (offline balance/gold_set tests + eval-discipline CI) and 476f (schema/shape validation).\n- AC5 (eval-live workflow_dispatch+weekly, non-blocking, cached, concurrency-capped, fork-safe, spend-cap docs): STRUCTURAL for 7402; covered by sibling 4569.\n\nUncovered-criterion sweep against the WHOLE roster: none. Every parent AC is covered either by this child (AC3 share) or by a named sibling (AC1->c156, AC2->476f, AC4->c156/476f, AC5->4569). This child's own ACs (solver context-injection + tool stubbing, versioned fixture corpus, adjudicated/provisional labels, offline FakeRunner tests) map cleanly onto parent AC3 / Scope 2.2+2.4 with no orphan scope."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782579797113969001,"uuid":"9869a63b-2539-4ad3-ab68-c48b940630a4"}